==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encrinoidea
<hw>En`cri*noid"e*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Encrinus</er> and <er>-oid</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>
<def>That order of the <class>Crinoidea</class> which includes most of
the living and many fossil forms, having jointed arms around the margin
of the oral disk; -- also called <altname>Brachiata</altname> and
<altname>Articulata</altname>. See <xex>Illusts</xex>. under
<er>Comatula</er> and <er>Crinoidea</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encrinus</ent>⟦br⟧
